==English==

===Noun===
'''Dog Days'''

# The days between early July and early September when [[Sirius]] (the [[Dog Star]]) rises and sets with the [[Sun]].
# Hot, lazy, days.
# A period of inactivity, laziness or stagnation.

====Translations====
*Finnish: [[mätäkuu]] (1, ''until late August''), [[kissanpäivät]] (3)

===Etymology===

Derived from the hot days (in the [[Northern Hemisphere]]) between early July and early September when Sirus (the [[Dog Star]]), in [[Canis Major]], rises and sets with the [[Sun]].

